<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — first OPVL together</h2>
  <p class="sub">Teacher-led whole-class activity. No choice board today — we do this together so the framework is modeled out loud before you try it alone in Block 2.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can name the four OPVL letters and what each asks of a source.
  </div>
  <figure class="content-figure">
    <img src="/assets/img/u0/u0-opvl-quadrant.svg" alt="OPVL quadrant: Origin — who made this, when, and what kind of thing is it; Purpose — why does it exist and for whom; Value — what is it genuinely good for answering; Limitations — what can it not tell you.">
  </figure>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">1</div>
      <div class="choice-title">A news article on a contested topic</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Seth Borenstein, <a href="https://apnews.com/article/ai-data-centers-environment-climate-footprint-a792f184a9f2833b5388dbae8b41ca95" target="_blank" rel="noopener">'Energy, water use and pollution of AI and data centers rival most countries'</a> (AP News, June 2026) — a UN report says the infrastructure behind AI uses electricity and water at the scale of entire countries; industry voices in the same article say it's worth it. We work through OPVL on this together — including on the tools this course itself uses. Printed excerpt (~400 words) provided in class; full article linked.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">2</div>
      <div class="choice-title">The report behind the article</div>
      <div class="choice-detail"><a href="/units/unit-0/unu-report-key-points/">Selected key points from the UNU-INWEH report itself</a> — the primary source the AP article summarizes. Same facts, different source type; the OPVL profiles diverge, and that divergence is today's lesson.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="choice placeholder">
      <span class="placeholder-tag">Placeholder</span>
      <div class="choice-letter">3</div>
      <div class="choice-title">A social media post on the same topic</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">TBD: tweet or short TikTok summary of the same topic. The third OPVL profile in the set — useful for contrast.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <figure class="content-figure">
    <img src="/assets/img/u0/u0-energy-chart.svg" alt="Bar chart from UNU report data: data centers used 448 terawatt-hours of electricity in 2025 with AI's share at 20 percent, projected to reach 945 terawatt-hours by 2030 with AI's share at 40 percent; a dashed reference line marks the annual residential electricity of all of Sub-Saharan Africa, about 172 terawatt-hours.">
    <figcaption>Drawn only from numbers in the UNU report (pp. 8–10) — which means you can check every part of this chart against the source. Try.</figcaption>
  </figure>
